      "to_id": "cec50b17:25",
      "content": "# Eval Phase 5 — `synapse eval apply` CLI deploy command\n\nYour orchestrator is cec50b17:0. Work inside `.synapse/worktrees/developer-25-eval-phase5`. Commit your changes there. Do not push.\n\n## Context\n\nPhases 1-3 are done. The S-Deck Deploy button calls `POST /api/proposals/:filename/deploy` which applies the patch, runs `synapse update .`, commits, resets the counter, and marks the proposal deployed. \n\nNow add a CLI equivalent so deploys can also be triggered headlessly: `synapse eval apply <proposal-file>`.\n\n## What to build (src/index.ts)\n\nIn the `synapse eval` commander command, add a subcommand `apply`:\n\n```\nprogram\n  .command('eval apply <proposal-file>')\n  .description('Apply a gate-approved proposal patch to the target rule file, commit, and reset the failure counter')\n  .action(async (proposalFile) => {\n    // 1. Read the proposal markdown\n    // 2. Parse Target-file and Proposed rule change (same logic as dashboard POST /deploy)\n    // 3. Append the proposed change to the target file\n    // 4. Run `synapse update .`\n    // 5. git commit with message: fix(<metric>): apply rule patch from proposal <basename>\n    // 6. Reset metric_failure_counts.count = 0 for that metric\n    // 7. Update Status: deployed in the proposal file\n    // 8. Print success summary\n  });\n```\n\nLook at `src/dashboard.ts` `POST /api/proposals/:filename/deploy` handler for the exact logic to replicate (it was just built in Phase 3). Keep the implementation consistent.\n\n## Build\n\n`npm run build` must pass clean.\n",
      "priority": 5,
      "created_at": 1780783413462,
      "read_at": 1780783415734,
